Package fi.imberg.juhani.ernu.interpreter.nodes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayAccessNode
    Accesses an array and either brings results or assigns nodes to the array.
    ArrayNode
    A node that describes an array, a generic list.
    AssignmentNode
    A node that assigns a node to an identifier.
    BlockNode
    Internal node for getting a singular value out of several statements.
    BooleanNode
    A node that represents a boolean.
    CallNode
    A node that calls a callable with arguments given to it.
    CaseNode
    A internal node that represents a single case of a match expression.
    ClassNode
    A node that represents an uninitialized class, that can be called upon to create an instance of the class.
    EnvironmentNode
    A node that holds an environment, specifically used with importing environments to another one.
    ForNode
    A for node represents a for loop.
    FunctionNode
    A function node holds a function, the arguments it takes and the statements that construct the functions body.
    IdentifierNode
    Identifier nodes are just basic labels that can be used for assignment and stuff.
    IfNode
    If nodes are just your everyday if/else/end structure.
    ImportNode
    Import nodes hold information about a import.
    MatchNode
    Match nodes hold case nodes, from which max one is evaluated.
    NullNode
    Null nodes are the nulls of ernu.
    NumberNode
    Number nodes represent an infinite precision rational number.
    ObjectAccessNode
    Accesses an object and either brings results or assigns nodes to the object.
    ObjectNode
    Represents an instance of a class.
    OperatorNode
    Represents an operation on two things, such as 3 + 2.
    PrefixNode
    Represents an prefix operation on a node.
    ProxyNode
    Proxy nodes proxy calls of functions into other namespaces.
    ReturnNode
    Return nodes throw ReturnExceptions to return values to functions.
    StringNode
    StringNode holds a string inside.
    WhileNode
    While nodes evaluate the body so long as the conditional is true.
